about: Initial state: only default user enabled with no password (typical factory state). The exact string may vary; this example reflects common defaults.
Authenticate as default using single-arg AUTH.
Now default has a password; LIST shows a hashed secret instead of “nopass”. Exact length and content vary; represented generically.
Now two users: default and alice, both enabled, both with hashed secrets. Exact strings vary; two array elements.
Basic data write while authenticated as alice.
Confirms data read works after AUTH.
Add a second valid password for alice (rotation overlap).
Remove all previous alice passwords and keep only newalicepass.
Remove all default passwords (temporarily unusable without new secret).
Single-arg AUTH now fails (no default passwords).
Final state: both default and alice enabled, both with passwords.
